\begin_layout Title
Status Consumption under uncertainty
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The role of income inequalities in status consumption has been explored
 less often in the literature on status consumption.
 Instead of considering status consumption a wasteful consumption, we view
 it in a context of income inequalities as a particular combination of upside
 risk choice and the choice to mitigate downside risks.
 by letting the consumer's risk aversion influence her choice we then look
 for constraints imposed by long-term resources in an economy on the competition
s for relative wealth.
 The effect of such constraints is used to explain how wide difference in
 wealth may discourage status consumption.
\end_layout

