 it may mean for the group of individuals aggregated over a higher level
 in the long-term.
 While a high-status individual in one localised context may not be high-status
 in another, the notions of power and net-asset-worth are shared across
 multiple contexts (societies, communities, nations etc.) in the long-run.
 We thus assume common reference point for all the consumers participating
 in status competitions.
