\begin_layout Standard
The consumer's projected future being subject to her private view means
 that the uncertainty perceived by the consumer may not be aligned with
 the risk in macroeconomic processes that determine her long-term income.
 This distinction in risk and the uncertainty perceived by the consumer
 is represented with a probability weighting function measuring the consumer's
 subjective non-linear response to observed risk.
 The notions of subjective probability that we wish to thus incorporate
 have been around at least since Keynes
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "KeynesProbability1921"
literal "false"

\end_inset

